<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=200&amp;p=1265#p1265"><![CDATA[
On the Pasofami emulator's page, I saw something interesting.  But as I cannot speak Japanese I had to rely on Babelfish, which was almost unhelpful.  But I guess that they are making RAM carts for the most common memory mappers, 0-4 and using USB to connect to a PC.  The PC is using Pasofami to send the ROMs to the cart.  At least this is what I can make out.  <br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.geocities.jp/pasofami77/usbdaiko.htm">http://www.geocities.jp/pasofami77/usbdaiko.htm</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Can anyone confirm or deny?[/code]<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=58">Great Hierophant</a> — Fri Feb 18, 2005 9:56 am</p><hr />
